    • Method Detail

      • getInstance

        public static RakeAPI getInstance(Context context,
                                  java.lang.String token,
                                  RakeAPI.Env env,
                                  RakeAPI.Logging logging)
        Create RakeAPI instance. (singleton per token)
        Parameters:
        context - Android Application Context
        token - Rake Token
        env - indicate whether RakeAPI send log to development server or live server If RakeAPI.Env.DEV used, RakeAPI will send log to development server (pg.rake.skplanet.com) If RakeAPI.Env.LIVE used, RakeAPI will send log to live server (rake.skplanet.com)
        logging - Logging.ENABLE or Logging.DISABLE
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if one of the parameters is NULL
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if uncaught exception occurred while initializing

      • setServerPort

        public void setServerPort(int port)
        Change server url's port value.
        If you have to send logs through specific non-charging server port, use this API.
        This only changes current instance's port value.(Endpoint.FREE).

        Parameters:
        port - non-charging port number (get it from admin)

      • getAutoProperties

        public JSONObject getAutoProperties(Context context)
                             throws JSONException
        Get auto collection properties which Rake Android collects by default. This method returns different results depending on token.
        Parameters:

        Returns:
        JSONObject auto collection properties by token.
        Throws:

      • excludeAutoProperties

        public void excludeAutoProperties(java.lang.String[] properties)
        Exclude auto collection properties from auto collection.
        For example, if you don't want to collect "device_id" automatically, call this method and send String[] including "device_id".
        Please call this method before track(JSONObject) if you want to apply your setting.
        Parameters:
        properties - auto collection property names to exclude from auto collection.
